{"body": "*bump*\r\n\r\nWould it make this any more compelling if I pointed out that this isn't just an optimization to reduce the number of objects created.   By running, eg, \r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nclient = company.clients.find_or_initialize_by_foo('bar')\r\nclient.save\r\ncompany.save\r\n```\r\n\r\nyou end up persisting two Client objects to the database - one in the return value from `find_or_initialize`, and one that's autosaved along with the `company.save`.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3769181", "created_at": "2012-02-01T23:06:01Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4543#issuecomment-3769181", "updated_at": "2012-02-01T23:07:14Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 4543, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jdelStrother", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/a9e5ce6f28587baa2a566eb4f2d76c13?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F269d837afada308dd4aeab28ca2d57e4.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/received_events", "gravatar_id": "a9e5ce6f28587baa2a566eb4f2d76c13", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jdelStrother", "type": "User", "id": 2377, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jdelStrother/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5238247abd3543c15100ec30"}, "id": 3769181, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4543"}
